# Domain & Blog Setup — sovereign-api.com

## Step 1: Cloudflare DNS Records (You do this)

Log into Cloudflare → `sovereign-api.com` → **DNS** tab → Add these records:

| Type | Name | Target | Proxy |
|------|------|--------|-------|
| **A** | `api` | `34.55.175.24` | ✅ Proxied |
| **CNAME** | `blog` | `hashnode.network` | ❌ DNS Only |
| **A** | `@` (root) | `34.55.175.24` | ✅ Proxied |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `blog` CNAME **must** be set to "DNS Only" (grey cloud), not "Proxied". Hashnode needs to handle its own SSL for custom domains.

**Result after this step:**
- `sovereign-api.com` → Your GCP Gateway
- `api.sovereign-api.com` → Your GCP Gateway
- `blog.sovereign-api.com` → Your Hashnode blog

## Step 2: Hashnode Custom Domain (You do this)

1. Go to Hashnode → Your blog → **Dashboard** → **Domain**
2. Enter: `blog.sovereign-api.com`
3. Hashnode will verify the CNAME and issue SSL automatically

